CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 2, 1975, pg. 13, reads: "Ms. Parks Retirement Tea - Mrs. Ernestine Parks, center, who spent many years as an educator with The Pittsburgh Board of Education, was honored recently with a gala Retirement Tea held at Centre Ave. YMCA. Others in picture, left to right are, Ms. Betty J. Williams, Pres. District 10 PTA; A. Bankston, second vice president PTSA; Ms. Lois Golden, vice principal, Schenley High; Ms. Frances Myers, president, PTSA; Andrew Parks, husband of honoree; Ms. J. Poole, first vice president of PTSA; Ms. M. Daniels, past V. P. PTSA; Ms. Agnes Davis, treasurer, PTSA and Ms. Viola Johnson, PTSA. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of seven women and four men, including honoree Ernestine Parks, and Andrew Parks in center, posed behind table for retirement tea party for Parks, at Centre Avenue YMCA
